<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53125f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53125f">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53125f"> 125(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mansuetude,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">La sixi&egrave;me semaine, il alla pr&egrave;s d&apos;un figuier o&ugrave;, souvent, se r&eacute;unissaient des chevriers. L&agrave;, des Dieux l&apos;attendaient, qui le salu&egrave;rent humblement. <p>Et il dit:</p> <p>&laquo;La <mark>mansu&eacute;tude</mark> est douce &agrave; qui conna&icirc;t la loi; la bienveillance est douce &agrave; qui sait voir; la mansu&eacute;tude est douce envers les cr&eacute;atures: la bienveillance est douce envers les cr&eacute;atures. <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 97</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: On the sixth week he addressed the gods, saying, Gentleness is sweet to one who knows the Law. </mm> </dd></dl>
